Pas2C pascal to C Source Code Converter

Build dependencies:

Bison, Yacc and gcc.

How To build:

just run build file.

converter currently inputs from stdin, and outputs to stdout. Easiest way to use is stream redirection via <|>.

Current Features:

Converting program %program_name%; to int main()
Converting main block of begin end to {}
Converting any valid sequence of begin end block to proper {}
Converting statements, regardless of the position relative to blocks.
	except the main block. every statement has to be in it.
Converting integer value operations:
	+,-,*,/ can be converted.
Converting integer definitions.
Converting integer assignments:
	assignments can be from one integer value or a result of two value operations "+ - / *".
Converting functions:
	currently only writeln implemented.
	only 1 parameter can be passed.
Converting of strings:
	only double quotes work, and alphanumerical characters are valid.
